<p><strong>Why this step matters:</strong> Duplicate sitemaps confuse crawlers and split your <a href="/glossary/crawl-budget/">crawl budget</a>. WordPress sites with both the core sitemap and a plugin sitemap active are a common source of this problem. Disable one before creating another.</p>
<p><strong>Pro tip:</strong> If your existing sitemap contains URLs returning 404 errors, redirects, or noindex tags, it needs replacement. A bad sitemap is worse than no sitemap.</p>
<h2>Step 2: Choose Your Sitemap Creation Method</h2>
<p>There are 3 ways to create an XML sitemap. The right method depends on your platform and technical comfort.</p>
<p><strong>Method A: CMS Plugin (Easiest)</strong></p>
<p>If you use WordPress, Shopify, Wix, Squarespace, or Webflow, your platform either auto-generates a sitemap or offers a plugin to do it.</p>
<div class="table-wrap"><table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Platform</th>
<th>Tool</th>
<th>Setup</th>
</tr>
</thead>
